From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000033 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Sun, 6 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] brcmfmac: don't error on a missing OPTIONAL firmware (clm_blob)

The SDIO fwreq marks the CLM blob BRCMF_FW_REQF_OPTIONAL and the driver
treats its absence as fine ("no clm_blob available ... limited
channels"). On the BCM4330 the CLM/regulatory data is compiled into the
firmware image -- no brcmfmac4330-sdio.clm_blob exists -- yet the
synchronous fallback path loaded it with request_firmware(), emitting
"Direct firmware load for brcm/brcmfmac4330-sdio.clm_blob failed with
error -2" on every boot. Use firmware_request_nowarn() for OPTIONAL
items at the fallback so the loader does not warn about a file the
driver itself declares optional. Non-optional items are unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/firmware.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/firmware.c
@@ -666,6 +666,16 @@
 	}
 
 fallback:
+	/*
+	 * The BCM4330 CLM/regulatory data is compiled into the firmware image
+	 * (no separate brcmfmac4330-sdio.clm_blob exists for this FWID), and the
+	 * driver flags that item BRCMF_FW_REQF_OPTIONAL and treats its absence as
+	 * fine ("no clm_blob available"). Don't emit a firmware-load error for an
+	 * item the driver itself declares optional -- use the nowarn loader so the
+	 * spurious "Direct firmware load ... failed with error -2" line is gone.
+	 */
+	if (cur->flags & BRCMF_FW_REQF_OPTIONAL)
+		return firmware_request_nowarn(fw, cur->path, fwctx->dev);
 	return request_firmware(fw, cur->path, fwctx->dev);
 }
 
